<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
    <title> ANKLE_PAIN_case_sheet_part</title>
    <link id="light-styles" rel="stylesheet" href="Case_sheet_styles.css">
    <link id="dark-styles" rel="alternate stylesheet" title="dark" href="Case_sheet_styles_dark.css">
    <script src="https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api"></script>
  </head>
  <body> <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode"> Dark Mode</button>
    <div class="General">
      <h3>1ST COMPLAINT: ANKLE PAIN</h3>
      <!-- S: Site -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Site</span>
        <span class="verbal">"Can you point with one finger to the exact
          location of the pain?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="ortho-specific">LATERAL (Outside): <span class="ortho-specific">Anterior
              Talofibular Ligament (ATFL) sprain, Peroneal tendinopathy, Fibular
              fracture</span></li>
          <li class="ortho-specific">MEDIAL (Inside): <span class="ortho-specific">Deltoid
              ligament sprain, Tibialis posterior tendinopathy, Medial malleolus
              fracture</span></li>
          <li class="ortho-specific">POSTERIOR (Back): <span class="ortho-specific">Achilles
              tendinopathy / rupture, Posterior impingement</span></li>
          <li class="ortho-specific">ANTERIOR (Front): <span class="ortho-specific">Syndesmosis
              (high ankle) sprain, Tibialis anterior tendinopathy</span></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- O: Onset -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>: Onset</span>
        <span class="verbal">"How did the pain start? Was there a specific
          injury, or did it come on gradually?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>ACUTE / TRAUMATIC:
            <ul>
              <li class="ortho-specific">Mechanism of injury? (e.g., twisting
                inward/inversion, outward/eversion, direct blow)</li>
              <li class="ortho-specific">Heard or felt a "pop" or "snap"?
                (Ligament tear, tendon rupture)</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>GRADUAL / INSIDIOUS (No trauma):
            <ul>
              <li class="ortho-specific">Overuse / change in activity?
                (Tendinopathy, stress fracture)</li>
              <li class="rheumatic">No preceding event? (Inflammatory arthritis,
                Gout)</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- D: Duration -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>: Duration</span>
        <span class="verbal">"How long has your ankle been painful?"</span> </li>
      <!-- A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>:
          Aggravating &amp; Relieving Factors</span> <span class="verbal">"What
          makes the pain worse or better?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>AGGRAVATING: </li>
          <ul>
            <li>USE (especially on uneven ground), standing for long periods.</li>
          </ul>
          <li>RELIEVING: </li>
          <ul>
            <li>Rest, ice, elevation, specific movements, medications.</li>
          </ul>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- C: Character -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>:
          Character</span> <span class="verbal">"What does the pain feel like?
          Is it a sharp pain, a dull ache, or burning?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="ortho-specific">SHARP / STABBING: <span class="ortho-specific">Acute
              injury, fracture, loose body</span></li>
          <li class="ortho-specific rheumatic">DULL ACHE: <span class="ortho-specific">Tendinopathy,
              Osteoarthritis</span></li>
          <li class="cns">BURNING / TINGLING / NUMBNESS: <span class="cns">Nerve
              involvement (Tarsal Tunnel Syndrome, radiculopathy)</span></li>
          <li class="rheumatic">THROBBING: <span class="rheumatic infectious">Inflammatory
              process (Gout, infection)</span></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- R: Radiation -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>:
          Radiation</span> <span class="verbal">"Does the pain travel anywhere,
          for example, up your leg or into your foot?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="cns">Pain radiating from the back suggests a lumbar spine
            cause</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- A: Associated Symptoms -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>:
          Associated Symptoms</span> <span class="verbal">"Besides the pain,
          have you noticed any swelling, instability, stiffness, or other
          issues?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="ortho-specific">LOCAL SYMPTOMS 
            <ul>
              <li class="ortho-specific">Swelling (immediate vs. delayed?)</li>
              <li class="ortho-specific">Bruising (where?)</li>
              <li class="ortho-specific">Instability (feeling of the ankle
                "giving way")</li>
              <li class="rheumatic ortho-specific">Stiffness (worse in the
                morning or after activity?)</li>
              <li class="ortho-specific">Locking, catching, or grinding
                sensations</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li class="h3 General">SYSTEMIC / INFLAMMATORY SYMPTOMS
            <ul>
              <li class="infectious">Fever, chills, malaise (Septic arthritis)</li>
              <li class="rheumatic">Pain or swelling in other joints?</li>
              <li class="rheumatic derma">Associated skin rashes?</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- P: Progression -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
          Progression</span> <span class="verbal">"Since it started, has the
          pain been getting better, worse, or staying the same?"</span> </li>
      <!-- P: Pattern -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Pattern</span>
        <span class="verbal">"Is the pain worse at any particular time of day?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="rheumatic">Worse in the morning, improves with movement
            -&gt; Inflammatory (e.g., Rheumatoid Arthritis)</li>
          <li class="ortho-specific">Worse at the end of the day or after
            activity -&gt; Mechanical (e.g., Osteoarthritis)</li>
          <li class="infectious ortho-specific">Constant, severe pain, worse at
            night -&gt; Red flag (Infection, Fracture, Tumor)</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- E: Effect on life -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>: Effect
          on Life</span> <span class="verbal">"How has this ankle pain affected
          your ability to walk, work, or do your hobbies?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="ortho-specific">Inability to bear weight? (Key Ottawa Rule
            question)</li>
          <li>Need for walking aids?</li>
          <li>Impact on sports or daily activities?</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- R: Red Flags -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Red
          Flags</span> <span class="verbal">"I need to ask some specific
          questions to make sure we're not missing anything serious."</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="ortho-specific emergency"><b>OTTAWA ANKLE RULES (for acute
              injury):</b>
            <ul>
              <li>Inability to bear weight for 4 steps (immediately after injury
                and in clinic)</li>
              <li>Bone tenderness at posterior edge of lateral or medial
                malleolus</li>
              <li>Bone tenderness at navicular (midfoot) or base of 5th
                metatarsal</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li class="infectious emergency">HOT, RED, SWOLLEN JOINT with FEVER
            -&gt; <b class="emergency">Septic Arthritis</b></li>
          <li class="cvs emergency">UNILATERAL CALF SWELLING, TENDERNESS -&gt; <b

              class="emergency">Deep Vein Thrombosis (DVT)</b></li>
          <li class="ortho-specific emergency">PALPABLE GAP in Achilles tendon
            after a "pop" -&gt; <b class="emergency">Achilles Rupture</b></li>
          <li class="cns ortho-specific emergency">NEW FOOT DROP or significant
            numbness/weakness -&gt; <b class="emergency">Nerve Injury /
              Compartment Syndrome</b></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- S: Scale -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Severity
          / Scale</span> <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10, how would
          you rate your pain right now?"</span> </li>
    </div>
    <script src="harsha_iframe_youtube_player.js"></script>
